1
00:01:33,207 --> 00:01:35,721
- What's up?
- I'm looking for Giovanni?

2
00:01:35,887 --> 00:01:40,438
- Where's Giovanni?
- Over there. He's expecting you.

3
00:01:46,047 --> 00:01:49,005
It should appear any minute no.
Come.

4
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:56,760
It's the only one of the seven islands
darker than the night.

5
00:02:07,847 --> 00:02:10,122
I wouldn't miss it for anything.

6
00:02:12,407 --> 00:02:13,840
Can you see it? There!

7
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:24,000
- Ginostra.
- It's the Sciarra del Fuoco.

8
00:02:24,847 --> 00:02:27,645
The last eruption
was 600 years back.

9
00:02:30,047 --> 00:02:34,404
If you come from the south part,
it looks like a pregnant woman,

10
00:02:34,887 --> 00:02:39,039
but from the north, it looks like
an old man ith a long beard.

11
00:02:45,927 --> 00:02:48,964
600 years, that's young,
for a volcano anyway.

12
00:04:13,407 --> 00:04:15,841
The first two months,
he lost the use of his legs.

13
00:04:16,287 --> 00:04:20,599
The X-rays showed nothing organic.
It as the trauma.

14
00:04:21,887 --> 00:04:23,843
- And now?
- He's fine.

15
00:04:24,727 --> 00:04:26,558
He spends his days here.

16
00:04:27,527 --> 00:04:29,119
How about his mental condition?

17
00:04:30,207 --> 00:04:32,926
He's a very secretive child.
That's him.

18
00:04:42,727 --> 00:04:45,525
He speaks English.
His father taught him.

19
00:04:45,687 --> 00:04:49,123
Ettore, you have visitors.
Get up.

20
00:04:58,287 --> 00:04:59,879
I'm Matt Benson.

21
00:05:06,487 --> 00:05:10,275
Come and get dressed. Excuse us,
we'll be right back. Let's go.

22
00:05:18,367 --> 00:05:21,518
I prefer to question the boy
in my house.

23
00:05:21,687 --> 00:05:23,359
I want to start tomorrow.

24
00:05:26,647 --> 00:05:29,957
We ask Rome,
but we decide in Lipari.

25
00:05:30,127 --> 00:05:33,597
Sicilians are a polite,
but proud people.

26
00:05:48,047 --> 00:05:50,083
My wife prepared this for you.

27
00:05:53,287 --> 00:05:55,881
It's mozzarella,
tomato and prosciutto.

28
00:06:03,247 --> 00:06:06,796
- Is it mozzarella di buffa?
- Yes, I think it is.

29
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:09,125
It's not buffa.

30
00:06:28,447 --> 00:06:29,880
Stop the car!

31
00:06:30,047 --> 00:06:31,366
I'm gonna be sick.

32
00:06:59,487 --> 00:07:00,602
You okay?

33
00:07:02,887 --> 00:07:05,765
Yes. We can go.

34
00:07:23,727 --> 00:07:26,605
Let's see. Milk, coffee, cereal.

35
00:07:26,767 --> 00:07:30,760
- These should last a few days.
- One more trip and it's done.

36
00:07:32,167 --> 00:07:35,443
- Do you want me to help you?
- No, thank you, it's okay.

37
00:07:42,567 --> 00:07:46,116
Did you sleep well?
Don't just stand there, come help.

38
00:07:46,447 --> 00:07:50,520
I found peanut butter.
It's amazing, in this tiny store.

39
00:07:50,687 --> 00:07:53,326
Tina would have killed me
if I hadn't found it.

40
00:07:53,487 --> 00:07:56,445
Paola, where is the phone?

41
00:07:58,527 --> 00:08:00,882
Ah, I found it.
Hello?

42
00:08:01,207 --> 00:08:04,643
Mom, hi.
Can you hold on a second?

43
00:08:05,447 --> 00:08:10,282
Ettore, go down to the cove
and try this out.

44
00:08:10,887 --> 00:08:14,118
I got you twelve gauges,
I hope it's okay.

45
00:08:14,487 --> 00:08:18,196
No, mom, they're hooks for fishing.
I was talking to Ettore,

46
00:08:18,367 --> 00:08:21,598
the boy that Matt's working with,
he's going to be staying here.

47
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:24,725
This island is the end of the world!
There's no water.

48
00:08:24,887 --> 00:08:28,436
They bring all the water by boat.
I just bought 200 bottles.

49
00:08:28,607 --> 00:08:32,486
Can I call you back mom,
I'm really busy? I love you.

50
00:08:35,647 --> 00:08:39,242
So the lady is letting you have
half of the house?

51
00:08:39,607 --> 00:08:42,440
- Is everything okay?
- Just one more bag.

52
00:08:42,607 --> 00:08:45,167
Do you mind hiding the bike?
I don't want Tina to see it.

53
00:08:45,327 --> 00:08:47,238
- I'll give it to her when Matt comes.
- Okay.

54
00:08:47,407 --> 00:08:49,762
She's going to love it. Thank you.

55
00:11:10,607 --> 00:11:11,756
What's going on?

56
00:11:11,927 --> 00:11:14,202
Excuse us. Let me speak.

57
00:11:15,207 --> 00:11:16,526
Sorry.

58
00:11:17,167 --> 00:11:19,078
- You all okay?
- We must go no.

59
00:11:19,247 --> 00:11:21,920
Thank you for your help.
We live at Santa Ginostra,

60
00:11:22,087 --> 00:11:25,238
you can come and visit us
on Sundays and Thursdays.

61
00:11:25,927 --> 00:11:27,440
You'll be welcome.

62
00:11:28,407 --> 00:11:30,875
Thank you. I will.

63
00:11:51,247 --> 00:11:52,600
Ettore,

64
00:11:56,367 --> 00:11:57,925
grab a chair.

65
00:11:59,287 --> 00:12:00,606
For what?

66
00:12:01,807 --> 00:12:03,286
We're going to ork.

67
00:12:11,767 --> 00:12:15,646
- Why not inside?
- Inside is my home.

68
00:12:15,807 --> 00:12:19,595
This is our office. Over here.

69
00:12:25,527 --> 00:12:27,165
Come here.

70
00:12:27,807 --> 00:12:29,525
In front of Ginostra.

71
00:12:37,287 --> 00:12:38,800
Ho do you like it here?

72
00:12:41,087 --> 00:12:43,681
No problem?
My wife, my daughter?

73
00:12:44,727 --> 00:12:46,126
No.

74
00:12:49,407 --> 00:12:50,965
Here, take a look.

75
00:12:53,767 --> 00:12:54,916
What is it?

76
00:12:56,447 --> 00:12:58,403
- Smell.
- I don't know.

77
00:12:58,927 --> 00:13:01,157
- Coke?
- It's not a game, come on.

78
00:13:03,487 --> 00:13:04,920
I'm not a dog.

79
00:13:05,887 --> 00:13:09,323
- Doesn't it ring any bells?
- I don't know what it is, okay?

80
00:13:12,327 --> 00:13:13,442
It's Semtex.

81
00:13:14,487 --> 00:13:17,877
Joe Manzella used this
to kill your family.

82
00:13:22,127 --> 00:13:24,197
Ho often did your dad
go to New York?

83
00:13:24,807 --> 00:13:27,560
- Leave my dad out of this.
- Twice a month on average.

84
00:13:27,807 --> 00:13:29,559
I have his passport here.

85
00:13:30,447 --> 00:13:31,960
You can have it.

86
00:13:47,327 --> 00:13:51,684
All I can do is put Joe Manzella
and his buddies away for a while.

87
00:13:51,847 --> 00:13:54,077
That's not enough for me.

88
00:13:56,687 --> 00:13:59,884
- You knew your dad was Cosa Nostra?
- No he wasn't. Never!

89
00:14:00,047 --> 00:14:03,642
He as the personal chef
of Frank and Joe Manzella.

90
00:14:03,807 --> 00:14:06,367
The mafia bosses of Ginostra.

91
00:14:06,527 --> 00:14:10,759
When Frank was forced to move
to New York, he sent for your father

92
00:14:10,927 --> 00:14:13,919
twice a month, to cook for him
and his family. They were real close.

93
00:14:14,087 --> 00:14:15,998
They were like
your family too, right?

94
00:14:17,607 --> 00:14:20,326
Mister, I am eleven years old,

95
00:14:21,607 --> 00:14:23,802
you asked me about my father.

96
00:14:24,607 --> 00:14:28,236
I loved him,
he loved me, and he's dead.

97
00:14:42,447 --> 00:14:44,483
Ettore, come up here.

98
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:48,516
What are you doing here?
I can't take my eyes off you.

99
00:14:48,927 --> 00:14:50,804
You don't like the fish?

100
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:55,361
This fish is up against
some merciless critic.

101
00:14:56,247 --> 00:14:59,239
Ettore's dad
was one of the best local chefs.

102
00:14:59,887 --> 00:15:02,526
Paola is a wonderful cook as well.

103
00:15:02,687 --> 00:15:06,521
- Yeah but his fish had...
- Fennel instead of lemon!

104
00:15:06,687 --> 00:15:08,803
I used hat I had.

105
00:15:14,967 --> 00:15:16,320
So, how long
are you going to stay?

106
00:15:16,487 --> 00:15:20,196
One week. Tina has to start school
on the twelfth.

107
00:15:20,647 --> 00:15:24,879
In one week, you'll have time
to see every beautiful sight.

108
00:15:26,287 --> 00:15:27,925
And no matter
how long you stay,

109
00:15:29,167 --> 00:15:31,442
you won't have time
to see all the ugly ones.

110
00:15:34,047 --> 00:15:37,722
Well, we'll be back
in three months, for Christmas.

111
00:15:38,807 --> 00:15:41,640
Four months.
Too long away from your husband.

112
00:15:42,927 --> 00:15:46,602
I am planning a long week-end
in New York, next month.

113
00:15:50,967 --> 00:15:54,004
I'm trying to learn
all the names of the volcanoes.

114
00:15:54,767 --> 00:15:56,519
I know there's Lipari,

115
00:15:57,647 --> 00:16:00,161
and Vulcano, and...

116
00:16:00,327 --> 00:16:02,477
- Allicudi...
- Allicudi.

117
00:16:02,647 --> 00:16:05,445
- Your turn.
- No, your turn.

118
00:16:05,607 --> 00:16:07,563
She's allergic to volcanoes.

119
00:16:09,247 --> 00:16:10,236
Are you afraid?

120
00:16:10,967 --> 00:16:14,801
No, more like impatient.

121
00:16:15,967 --> 00:16:18,720
Wondering everyday
if it's going to erupt,

122
00:16:19,527 --> 00:16:23,486
when we know we have one chance
in a million to see it wake up.

123
00:16:24,887 --> 00:16:28,482
It's like having a ticket for a show
that may never open.

124
00:16:28,647 --> 00:16:30,160
Isn't that better?

125
00:16:30,847 --> 00:16:33,122
Actually,
I would like to see it blow up.

126
00:16:36,687 --> 00:16:38,962
No, here boredom
catches up with you

127
00:16:40,007 --> 00:16:41,838
and it won't let go.

128
00:16:42,567 --> 00:16:44,478
It grows on you.

129
00:16:46,927 --> 00:16:48,076
Enough!

130
00:16:50,047 --> 00:16:52,436
He loves this country
more than I do.

131
00:16:53,447 --> 00:16:55,005
And maybe
more than he loves me.

132
00:16:55,167 --> 00:16:59,365
- What are you talking about?
- I thank volcanoes for one thing.

133
00:17:00,687 --> 00:17:01,722
The "Santa Ginostra".

134
00:17:04,527 --> 00:17:06,404
- Who makes this wine?
- The nuns.

135
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:10,003
Taste before investigating,
Mr. FBI Man.

136
00:17:10,167 --> 00:17:12,761
In Sicily, do as Sicilians do.

137
00:17:18,487 --> 00:17:21,877
Elena and Giovanni
make quite a pair.

138
00:17:22,327 --> 00:17:26,923
- He was a little pushy.
- That didn't seem to bother you.

139
00:17:32,567 --> 00:17:36,276
Tina feels right at home here,
nothing phases her.

140
00:17:50,727 --> 00:17:52,922
She really likes Ettore.

141
00:17:54,607 --> 00:17:58,646
I'm sure your work with him
will go fine. Children sense things.

142
00:18:01,807 --> 00:18:03,718
Oh, I love this place.

143
00:18:05,487 --> 00:18:10,436
- Do you know how owns the house?
- No, I don't.

144
00:18:11,727 --> 00:18:14,525
It's going to be too big for you
when we're gone.

145
00:18:16,847 --> 00:18:19,042
I'm glad you've come.

146
00:18:23,167 --> 00:18:25,965
We have to be careful
with Tina here.

147
00:18:26,407 --> 00:18:29,638
Giovanni says it goes down 500 feet.

148
00:20:37,167 --> 00:20:39,522
You could have died up there.

149
00:20:40,087 --> 00:20:42,999
I took the night ferry
and lost my way.

150
00:20:48,087 --> 00:20:51,079
I thought the convent as higher up.

151
00:20:52,927 --> 00:20:57,682
Santa Ginostra is a sanctuary,
protected from all, even the FBI.

152
00:20:59,727 --> 00:21:02,400
I was told anyone could come here
on Thursdays.

153
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:06,446
I'm just an ordinary visitor.
And a neighbor now too.

154
00:21:08,607 --> 00:21:09,926
Follow me.

155
00:21:12,047 --> 00:21:14,800
- Do you know our wine?
- Yes.

156
00:21:15,447 --> 00:21:18,405
- And our perfumes?
- No I don't.

157
00:21:23,727 --> 00:21:25,957
We banished Rome's God.

158
00:21:27,247 --> 00:21:28,919
We worship the abyss.

159
00:21:36,367 --> 00:21:37,402
Sister Chiara.

160
00:21:38,887 --> 00:21:43,597
Take this visitor to our shop.
You may find something for your wife.

161
00:21:49,087 --> 00:21:50,406
I'll make you a deal...

162
00:21:52,727 --> 00:21:54,126
as a neighbor.

163
00:22:32,487 --> 00:22:34,682
This is where
the flowers are pressed.

164
00:22:34,887 --> 00:22:39,039
We mix jasmine, mimosa,
local roses and many others.

165
00:22:40,967 --> 00:22:42,400
Our composition is a...

166
00:22:44,127 --> 00:22:45,799
a secret.

167
00:22:47,567 --> 00:22:50,718
Those wild flowers remind us that

168
00:22:50,887 --> 00:22:55,438
before the lava flow, Ginostra
was covered with trees and meadows.

169
00:23:00,207 --> 00:23:02,926
Here you are.
The choice is yours.

170
00:24:25,807 --> 00:24:29,686
Tell Joe Manzella
I'm here to get him.

171
00:24:58,167 --> 00:24:59,646
Did you sleep well?

172
00:25:01,047 --> 00:25:05,006
- I went back to bed.
- I missed the ferry.

173
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:12,764
Why didn't you take the helicopter?

174
00:25:15,087 --> 00:25:16,918
It wasn't available.

175
00:25:24,567 --> 00:25:26,762
What are we going to
talk about today?

176
00:25:28,207 --> 00:25:30,038
How about, you.

177
00:25:31,567 --> 00:25:36,038
Why have you brought your family?
It could be dangerous, if I talk.

178
00:25:40,047 --> 00:25:42,038
Don't you worry about that.

179
00:26:27,367 --> 00:26:30,120
Okay. Paola!

180
00:26:35,407 --> 00:26:37,557
- Paola!
- I'm here.

181
00:26:41,287 --> 00:26:44,836
- Look at the shells we found!
- Ah, ho beautiful!

182
00:26:49,487 --> 00:26:51,045
His specialties?

183
00:26:52,327 --> 00:26:54,238
I can't talk about it.

184
00:26:55,487 --> 00:26:56,636
You can.

185
00:26:57,767 --> 00:26:59,598
I blacked out just after.

186
00:27:00,767 --> 00:27:03,520
I don't remember a thing
until the hospital.

187
00:27:03,687 --> 00:27:05,803
Before the explosion.

188
00:27:06,687 --> 00:27:07,722
Tell me.

189
00:27:09,647 --> 00:27:13,276
- I'd rather give you names.
- I'm not interested in names now.

190
00:27:19,287 --> 00:27:21,437
I didn't think of my mother,

191
00:27:22,967 --> 00:27:24,480
I looked for my father.

192
00:27:27,127 --> 00:27:29,038
I heard him shouting,

193
00:27:30,487 --> 00:27:33,604
he was shouting to my sisters
to get out.

194
00:27:35,247 --> 00:27:38,159
The flames didn't seem
to touch him,

195
00:27:38,887 --> 00:27:41,447
he was holding my sisters
in his arms.

196
00:27:42,727 --> 00:27:45,082
They were like two balls of fire
in his hands.

197
00:27:46,047 --> 00:27:47,958
The flames of hell.

198
00:27:50,447 --> 00:27:52,324
Then, all of a sudden,

199
00:27:54,847 --> 00:27:57,805
he weakened and fell forward
over the wheel

200
00:27:59,647 --> 00:28:01,717
and that's all I saw.

201
00:28:02,807 --> 00:28:05,560
The explosion hurt me, here.

202
00:28:08,447 --> 00:28:10,005
And I blacked out.

203
00:28:13,887 --> 00:28:16,082
What happened that morning?

204
00:28:20,247 --> 00:28:21,396
What?

205
00:28:22,447 --> 00:28:25,519
They left me alive
to kill the bastards who did it.

206
00:28:34,047 --> 00:28:35,116
Come over here.

207
00:28:41,327 --> 00:28:44,603
What makes you think
Joe Manzella wasn't alone?

208
00:28:44,767 --> 00:28:48,396
He is the boss of seven islands.
Everyone works for him.

209
00:28:50,367 --> 00:28:54,804
Did your father ever mention anybody
special, he might have met here

210
00:28:54,967 --> 00:28:56,764
that stands out, maybe someone
outside the Cosa Nostra,

211
00:28:57,767 --> 00:28:59,644
maybe from the police?

212
00:29:03,047 --> 00:29:04,719
Marty Del Piero?

213
00:29:08,567 --> 00:29:09,682
No.

214
00:29:13,927 --> 00:29:18,045
Give me some names of the people
who were closest to Manzella.

215
00:29:20,287 --> 00:29:21,515
Two names.

216
00:29:23,207 --> 00:29:26,836
Beppe Puglisi.
Santo Ragusa.

217
00:29:33,287 --> 00:29:34,356
Okay.

218
00:29:34,687 --> 00:29:36,200
That'll be all for today.

219
00:29:37,447 --> 00:29:40,200
I'll check them out
with the D.A.

220
00:29:57,767 --> 00:30:00,759
Ginostra is the most
beautiful island in the world.

221
00:30:02,367 --> 00:30:04,881
Ettore was born here,
like the Manzellas,

222
00:30:05,607 --> 00:30:07,325
and he was a happy child.

223
00:30:16,927 --> 00:30:21,000
But the Manzellas forced the people
into silence and submission.

224
00:30:24,607 --> 00:30:25,926
Look, can you see there?

225
00:30:26,287 --> 00:30:29,438
That's Ettore's house.
It's an old mill.

226
00:30:29,607 --> 00:30:32,075
His uncles and cousins live there.

227
00:30:32,247 --> 00:30:35,398
They washed every stone
to purify it,

228
00:30:35,567 --> 00:30:39,879
to erase memories of Ettore's father
after he betrayed the Mafia.

229
00:30:49,967 --> 00:30:54,279
Now, do you want to fly over
to see the convent on the other side?

230
00:30:55,087 --> 00:30:56,440
No, later.

231
00:30:57,847 --> 00:31:00,998
I have to get to the D.A.
to check out some names.

232
00:31:18,327 --> 00:31:20,158
What do you know about me?

233
00:31:20,567 --> 00:31:23,161
Well... your name, your age...

234
00:31:23,847 --> 00:31:25,166
Not much.

235
00:31:26,527 --> 00:31:28,119
And... the accident.

236
00:31:29,047 --> 00:31:30,480
It wasn't an accident.

237
00:31:33,767 --> 00:31:36,725
Doesn't your husband
tell you nothing? Never?

238
00:31:36,887 --> 00:31:41,005
About his job? Not really.
Only what you'll tell me.

239
00:31:52,167 --> 00:31:55,603
- Why did Matt come here?
- I don't know exactly,

240
00:31:55,807 --> 00:31:59,482
- to investigate.
- He came from New York just for me?

241
00:32:00,087 --> 00:32:03,841
Yes, I guess.
Are you impressed?

242
00:32:04,007 --> 00:32:06,521
My dad went to cook in New York
lots of times,

243
00:32:06,687 --> 00:32:09,281
but I'm sure
that's not the only reason.

244
00:32:09,447 --> 00:32:12,041
Don't you think
you should ask Matt?

245
00:32:13,167 --> 00:32:14,566
I'm going to bed.

246
00:32:14,727 --> 00:32:17,719
I put some blankets in your room
in case it gets cold.

247
00:32:18,927 --> 00:32:20,485
Sweet dreams.

248
00:32:24,927 --> 00:32:28,397
- Who is it?
