01:00:40,287 --> 01:00:44,360
I don't want my wife to know
anything about this.

489
01:00:44,687 --> 01:00:48,726
I'll tell her what a shit you are!
Let go of me! You're choking me.

490
01:00:50,007 --> 01:00:53,761
Listen to me! Listen to me!

491
01:00:54,807 --> 01:00:58,766
If my wife or anybody
finds about this,

492
01:00:58,927 --> 01:01:01,282
you won't get what you want.

493
01:01:01,527 --> 01:01:04,439
You won't get what you want.
Listen to me.

494
01:01:04,767 --> 01:01:08,237
I'm the only one here who can
help you get Manzella!

495
01:01:11,207 --> 01:01:12,765
I'm the only one!

496
01:01:23,487 --> 01:01:27,480
I'll help you get what you want.
We'll get him.

497
01:01:35,087 --> 01:01:36,520
I promise you.

498
01:01:39,847 --> 01:01:41,246
Go to sleep.

499
01:01:52,087 --> 01:01:55,159
- You rang?
- Giovanni is not home?

500
01:01:56,207 --> 01:01:57,242
No.

501
01:01:57,847 --> 01:02:00,998
- I was going to number 18.
- Oh. Okay.

502
01:02:02,047 --> 01:02:03,275
Will you come on Sunday?

503
01:02:04,527 --> 01:02:07,724
We're having a party by the islands.

504
01:02:09,167 --> 01:02:10,361
Thanks.

505
01:02:10,927 --> 01:02:14,476
- Matt. I wanted to tell you...
- Yes?

506
01:02:16,687 --> 01:02:18,245
We can help you.

507
01:02:41,207 --> 01:02:42,925
Tischka! Cut it out!

508
01:02:48,527 --> 01:02:49,642
Come in.

509
01:02:55,407 --> 01:02:58,240
- Bring the mower back up!
- No!

510
01:02:58,407 --> 01:03:00,637
Who the hell's going to steal it?

511
01:03:02,287 --> 01:03:05,916
My wife... Susanna...
for forty years now.

512
01:03:06,087 --> 01:03:08,806
- Matt Benson.
- Nice to meet you.

513
01:03:17,447 --> 01:03:19,324
- Here, have a seat.
- Thanks.

514
01:03:22,527 --> 01:03:25,121
Elena told me about you yesterday.

515
01:03:26,847 --> 01:03:29,122
- What will you have to drink?
- Same as you.

516
01:03:29,327 --> 01:03:31,795
Honey, could you bring us
a couple of whiskeys!

517
01:03:33,687 --> 01:03:35,040
So...

518
01:03:36,807 --> 01:03:39,241
You see... Retirement.

519
01:03:43,687 --> 01:03:48,124
I met him for the first time...
thirty-five years ago?

520
01:03:48,407 --> 01:03:50,875
- Thirty.
- Thirty. On Malcolm Street.

521
01:03:51,527 --> 01:03:54,678
When I was tailing
Giuseppe D'Alba.

522
01:03:55,647 --> 01:03:57,524
Honey, could you leave us?

523
01:04:09,727 --> 01:04:14,084
It wasn't me who betrayed you, Matt.
You believe me?

524
01:04:18,247 --> 01:04:21,398
I received your request to protect
Ettore's family,

525
01:04:21,567 --> 01:04:25,879
when his father decided to enter
the federal witness program.

526
01:04:26,327 --> 01:04:29,637
But you know how slowly
things move here.

527
01:04:30,327 --> 01:04:34,639
Before we could do anything, it had
all blown up in our faces, literally.

528
01:04:36,607 --> 01:04:38,598
Two months later,
I was due for retirement,

529
01:04:38,767 --> 01:04:43,761
I didn't speed up the investigation,
and understand... in Lipari,

530
01:04:45,727 --> 01:04:48,560
we already have
too much on our plates.

531
01:04:54,207 --> 01:04:59,076
I've lost a son
in this dirty fucking war

532
01:05:00,287 --> 01:05:05,122
and, on his grave,
I tell you it wasn't me.

533
01:05:07,807 --> 01:05:09,206
Do you believe me?

534
01:05:12,727 --> 01:05:14,479
Yeah, I believe you.

535
01:05:22,087 --> 01:05:23,406
They love sugar.

536
01:05:25,447 --> 01:05:28,837
You're making a big mistake
having that kid at your house.

537
01:05:33,727 --> 01:05:37,436
You're an American,
an easy prey.

538
01:05:38,527 --> 01:05:42,964
They'll trap you in that den of yours
and choke you on their own soil.

539
01:06:10,967 --> 01:06:13,720
It always rains for re-enactments.

540
01:06:26,167 --> 01:06:29,239
They were all against me
coming here.

541
01:06:29,407 --> 01:06:33,366
All of them, except Giovanni.

542
01:06:34,647 --> 01:06:38,117
I don't know why he's here. He could
have had a great career in New York.

543
01:06:39,527 --> 01:06:44,078
His father as a cop in Gela.
Got killed when Giovanni was eight.

544
01:06:53,567 --> 01:06:57,003
It always rains for re-enactments.
This sucks!

545
01:07:01,407 --> 01:07:05,195
I'll have two cops in the car
with you, to play your family.

546
01:07:05,807 --> 01:07:08,480
Don't try to remember
what happened,

547
01:07:09,047 --> 01:07:11,641
just do what comes naturally.

548
01:07:12,127 --> 01:07:16,598
- Did you come by my house Saturday?
- Yeah, I wanted to talk to you.

549
01:07:16,847 --> 01:07:18,075
What about?

550
01:07:19,647 --> 01:07:21,399
Well, I'll tell you later.

551
01:07:31,407 --> 01:07:34,126
When I give that signal,
send the car okay.

552
01:07:34,287 --> 01:07:37,199
The virgins from Santa Ginostra
aren't here yet.

553
01:07:38,887 --> 01:07:42,721
The nuns ere the first to arrive
after the explosion.

554
01:07:42,887 --> 01:07:44,764
Go on, I wanna see the kid.
I'll catch up.

555
01:07:44,927 --> 01:07:48,317
Okay, We'll start without them.
Alright, go!

556
01:08:03,967 --> 01:08:05,559
What is it now?

557
01:08:07,487 --> 01:08:11,639
- Nothing. Close your window.
- It was open. It was sunny that day.

558
01:08:21,167 --> 01:08:24,239
<i>Dino, Leonardo,
the boy's cold. What do I do?</i>

559
01:08:24,407 --> 01:08:25,920
Is everybody ready?

560
01:08:26,087 --> 01:08:27,566
<i>Yes.</i>

561
01:08:28,127 --> 01:08:30,322
Okay, start the car moving.

562
01:08:41,247 --> 01:08:43,841
- Manzella's here.
- Where?

563
01:08:44,007 --> 01:08:47,886
On Ginostra. We are planning
to set him up again.

564
01:08:50,087 --> 01:08:52,647
You are supposed to keep out
of the operation.

565
01:08:52,807 --> 01:08:54,559
It's a request from the D.A.

566
01:08:56,847 --> 01:08:58,565
Hey, hold on!

567
01:09:00,247 --> 01:09:01,396
Oh fuck, the kid's jumped out.

568
01:09:01,927 --> 01:09:04,885
Hey, hold on!

569
01:09:06,687 --> 01:09:08,086
Come here!

570
01:09:13,287 --> 01:09:15,005
Who was watching him?

571
01:09:15,167 --> 01:09:18,125
- He went that way.
- Where?

572
01:10:05,647 --> 01:10:07,000
It's all right.

573
01:10:16,567 --> 01:10:18,239
We'll get them,

574
01:10:18,727 --> 01:10:22,436
believe me.
On my daughter's head.

575
01:10:41,807 --> 01:10:44,446
I'd prefer you to go back sooner.

576
01:10:44,967 --> 01:10:47,640
I've had a great time
with you and Tina here,

577
01:10:47,807 --> 01:10:50,560
but things are getting
more difficult.

578
01:10:50,727 --> 01:10:53,924
But I told you, Giovanni
said it was safe...

579
01:10:54,087 --> 01:10:56,965
Of course Giovanni
would be delighted if you stayed.

580
01:10:57,127 --> 01:10:59,402
Don't tell me you're jealous!

581
01:11:01,247 --> 01:11:04,557
Something's going on.
You don't work with Ettore anymore.

582
01:11:04,727 --> 01:11:08,800
- You don't pay attention to him now.
- I want to give him some time.

583
01:11:08,967 --> 01:11:12,801
It's not easy for him,
hat he has to tell me.

584
01:11:12,967 --> 01:11:15,322
I feel like you're
keeping things from me.

585
01:11:15,487 --> 01:11:20,277
- Important things, between you two.
- What do you mean? There's nothing.

586
01:11:22,287 --> 01:11:26,963
So, you were happy
that I was here

587
01:11:27,727 --> 01:11:30,878
- and no you want me to leave.
- Yes,

588
01:11:32,447 --> 01:11:34,517
I want you to go home!

589
01:11:49,807 --> 01:11:52,844
Oh, Lord,
Bless and sanctify this act

590
01:11:53,007 --> 01:11:55,965
for the purification of my body
and soul.

591
01:12:33,967 --> 01:12:36,686
Take it, it's yours.

592
01:12:38,007 --> 01:12:39,963
Look how nice it is.

593
01:12:40,927 --> 01:12:44,283
It's an angel.
I give you an angel.

594
01:12:45,807 --> 01:12:49,482
Give it life and tenderness.

595
01:12:54,327 --> 01:12:55,965
Keep it.

596
01:12:59,447 --> 01:13:01,802
So that it may always eat.

597
01:13:02,687 --> 01:13:04,757
So that it will always be free.

598
01:13:39,007 --> 01:13:42,716
- I want to go home!
- You don't like it here?

599
01:13:43,607 --> 01:13:46,201
My home is over there, not here.

600
01:13:48,367 --> 01:13:51,837
- We have to give them time to forget.
- Forget what?

601
01:13:53,487 --> 01:13:56,843
Time for you to forget
what they have done again.

602
01:14:00,647 --> 01:14:03,081
They don't want me
to go to Ginostra.

603
01:14:03,367 --> 01:14:06,757
What do you want to do there.
There is nothing to see.

604
01:14:21,767 --> 01:14:25,476
The Manzellas' father was the richest
building contractor in Sicily.

605
01:14:25,847 --> 01:14:30,045
But that wasn't enough for him,
he wanted to conquer Naples.

606
01:14:31,407 --> 01:14:35,639
He got involved in politics. He even
tried to get elected mayor,

607
01:14:35,967 --> 01:14:39,801
but the Neapolitans sent him
back home to his island.

608
01:14:42,327 --> 01:14:46,605
After that,
he decided to build a bridge,

609
01:14:47,087 --> 01:14:49,920
so he would never have to
set foot in it again.

610
01:14:50,767 --> 01:14:54,316
When he had to drive from the airport
to get a boat for Ginostra,

611
01:14:54,487 --> 01:14:56,205
he would throw his garbage
out of the window,

612
01:14:56,367 --> 01:14:59,325
as if the city was
just one big dump.

613
01:15:02,127 --> 01:15:05,597
What do we do about that pretty
little nun from Santa Ginostra?

614
01:15:07,327 --> 01:15:12,196
Let her run free. Soon, I'll be
able to arrest her for complicity.

615
01:15:14,207 --> 01:15:16,357
Why haven't you arrested her yet?

616
01:15:16,807 --> 01:15:21,801
- I mean her complicity with you.
- With me?

617
01:15:23,647 --> 01:15:26,241
Well, at the station they're saying
that you instructed the pilot

618
01:15:26,407 --> 01:15:28,523
to fly over the Ginostra convent

619
01:15:28,687 --> 01:15:31,121
to sabotage Manzella's arrest.

620
01:15:31,287 --> 01:15:33,562
That's the "unofficial" version.

621
01:15:34,287 --> 01:15:36,164
You're investigating me?

622
01:15:37,367 --> 01:15:39,517
If you keep missing Manzella,

623
01:15:39,687 --> 01:15:43,202
you'll have more time
to investigate us.

624
01:16:00,167 --> 01:16:02,317
I'll climb down, I love it.

625
01:16:05,807 --> 01:16:08,002
How do you make "Bucatini"?

626
01:16:08,607 --> 01:16:10,325
A la matriciana,

627
01:16:10,847 --> 01:16:13,839
Al pesto, with seafood...

628
01:16:14,327 --> 01:16:16,158
And with sunfloer seeds?

629
01:16:16,447 --> 01:16:20,838
With sunflower seeds?
Only in Milano they can eat that.

630
01:16:23,287 --> 01:16:27,280
The dinner when they decided
to kill Greco, they served bucatini

631
01:16:28,087 --> 01:16:30,396
with sunflower seeds.

632
01:16:33,487 --> 01:16:37,719
The earth on volcanoes
is too black for sunflowers to grow.

633
01:17:45,287 --> 01:17:46,720
Fourth floor!

634
01:17:49,327 --> 01:17:51,158
Fourth floor!

635
01:17:52,447 --> 01:17:54,597
Hey! Fourth floor!

636
01:17:57,287 --> 01:17:58,959
Fourth!

637
01:19:53,127 --> 01:19:57,006
Hey! Where's Giovanni,
is he alright?

638
01:19:57,167 --> 01:20:00,239
- Where?
- He's there. He's okay.

639
01:20:28,887 --> 01:20:30,843
Why did you scream?

640
01:20:39,367 --> 01:20:40,686
You screamed.

641
01:20:42,007 --> 01:20:44,646
- I heard you scream.
- Let go of me! You're crazy!

642
01:20:49,927 --> 01:20:51,201
I fell.

643
01:21:16,567 --> 01:21:20,799
Yes operator. Can you get me
the District Attorney?

644
01:21:29,127 --> 01:21:30,845
<i>District Attorney.</i>

645
01:21:31,007 --> 01:21:33,601
Hello? Is Matt Benson there?

646
01:21:35,207 --> 01:21:36,925
<i>What name?</i>

647
01:21:37,087 --> 01:21:41,160
It's very urgent.
This is Jessie, his wife.

648
01:21:41,327 --> 01:21:44,876
And I need to talk to him.
It's really important.

649
01:21:45,047 --> 01:21:46,366
<i>One moment.</i>

650
01:21:46,527 --> 01:21:51,317
Thank you. You see,
he hasn't come back.

651
01:21:53,687 --> 01:21:57,726
And I'm very frightened.
It's just that...

652
01:21:57,887 --> 01:21:59,320
<i>Hold on, please.</i>

653
01:21:59,487 --> 01:22:03,844
It's just not like him to not call.
So can you tell me anything?

654
01:22:04,727 --> 01:22:08,436
<i>Matt Benson has been
taken off the case. Good-Bye Ma'am.</i>

655
01:22:10,647 --> 01:22:12,239
I hate you.

656
01:22:47,687 --> 01:22:50,326
Your dog's not barking anymore.

657
01:22:51,327 --> 01:22:54,683
Maybe you killed him.
You would.

658
01:23:03,007 --> 01:23:06,124
The Grecos' killing
has really hurt me,

659
01:23:06,647 --> 01:23:08,444
it has hurt me bad.

660
01:23:10,047 --> 01:23:12,880
The kid's my responsibility now.

661
01:23:15,727 --> 01:23:18,321
I don't care about the kid.

662
01:23:21,527 --> 01:23:23,961
I would like the two of you
to meet.

663
01:23:26,487 --> 01:23:27,806
What for?

664
01:23:29,287 --> 01:23:32,597
You could say
he's both our responsibility now.

665
01:23:34,927 --> 01:23:36,645
I want to be alone.

666
01:23:39,807 --> 01:23:41,240
Go away.

667
01:23:49,287 --> 01:23:51,403
Ettore's family's tickets.

668
01:23:51,567 --> 01:23:54,843
They were supposed to leave
three days after the car bomb.

669
01:23:55,007 --> 01:23:56,406
Nobody's used them.

670
01:24:37,767 --> 01:24:42,238
I had an affair with a woman
in New York, twenty years ago.

671
01:24:44,407 --> 01:24:46,443
She had a baby.

672
01:24:47,407 --> 01:24:51,400
A baby I didn't want
and I didn't want to see.

673
01:24:53,567 --> 01:24:55,080
It was a girl,

674
01:24:56,487 --> 01:24:58,682
and she grew up alone,

675
01:25:00,207 --> 01:25:02,596
between Brooklyn and Queens.

676
01:25:10,647 --> 01:25:13,764
My wife would have died
if I had told her.

677
01:25:15,327 --> 01:25:16,680
I didn't say anything

678
01:25:18,047 --> 01:25:23,041
but I only accepted the missions
that would keep me here, to forget.

679
01:25:27,367 --> 01:25:30,165
The girl's mother
never held it against me.

680
01:25:32,927 --> 01:25:36,158
We hadn't planned anything,
it just happened

681
01:25:37,207 --> 01:25:39,277
and the girl,

682
01:25:44,887 --> 01:25:46,445
I never knew,

683
01:25:48,527 --> 01:25:52,759
but I think
she must have hated me.

684
01:26:02,767 --> 01:26:06,885
Then, when she turned seventeen
she became beautiful

685
01:26:08,487 --> 01:26:12,002
and she met Franck Manzella.

686
01:26:13,847 --> 01:26:18,204
My daughter became
Franck Manzella's mistress.

687
01:26:20,487 --> 01:26:23,843
Then his brother Joe's mistress,

688
01:26:29,247 --> 01:26:33,286
and they used her
in their business.

689
01:26:43,767 --> 01:26:46,804
When you called me
to protect the Grecos,

690
01:26:47,567 --> 01:26:49,922
because the father
as going to talk,

691
01:26:50,807 --> 01:26:54,959
I knew he would denounce
Joe and my daughter.

692
01:26:58,287 --> 01:27:00,403
I didn't hesitate.

693
01:27:04,367 --> 01:27:06,164
You see...

694
01:27:12,487 --> 01:27:14,318
she is my daughter.

695
01:27:32,407 --> 01:27:34,079
Lie down.

696
01:28:18,367 --> 01:28:21,803
Tomorrow,
I'm going to have you arrested.

697
01:28:49,327 --> 01:28:53,366
Where's the lizard?
Where is it?

698
01:29:02,327 --> 01:29:04,158
Where's the lizard?

699
01:29:05,287 --> 01:29:07,437
Maybe he'd like some toast
and butter,

700
01:29:07,607 --> 01:29:10,440
what do you think,
scrambled eggs?

701
01:29:11,127 --> 01:29:13,595
Okay. Here,
you sit over here darling.

702
01:29:14,207 --> 01:29:17,279
Get your tush up
don't fall off.

703
01:29:17,527 --> 01:29:20,485
Okay, put a little milk in the bowl,

704
01:29:20,887 --> 01:29:25,881
okay let's see, okay lambsky,
here we go. Breakfast.

705
01:29:27,447 --> 01:29:30,359
There's a plane tomorrow at 9:00.
We're taking it.

706
01:29:31,127 --> 01:29:33,038
- Wait...
- We're taking it!

707
01:29:34,927 --> 01:29:36,246
I'll call Giovanni.

708
01:29:36,407 --> 01:29:39,365
- Do it now.
- Nice milk...

709
01:29:39,847 --> 01:29:41,166
Lamby.

710
01:29:41,407 --> 01:29:44,046
- Come on lamby.
- I'm leaving.

711
01:29:44,207 --> 01:29:47,438
- You're imagining things.
- I'm afraid here, of everything,

712
01:29:47,607 --> 01:29:49,165
- even afraid of you.
- He doesn't want any milk.

713
01:29:52,567 --> 01:29:55,001
I don't know what's happening
but its...

714
01:29:58,047 --> 01:30:00,083
How far will you go?

715
01:30:01,687 --> 01:30:03,120
Forgive me.

716
01:30:05,207 --> 01:30:08,802
The sea is getting rough. If we
don't go we could be stuck here.

717
01:30:08,967 --> 01:30:11,083
What about Ettore?

718
01:30:11,687 --> 01:30:13,279
You wanted all this.

719
01:30:14,407 --> 01:30:18,639
There is nothing I can do for him.
Don't use him now.

720
01:30:20,527 --> 01:30:22,085
Call Giovanni.

721
01:30:48,687 --> 01:30:49,961
Giovanni. Matt.

722
01:30:50,127 --> 01:30:51,162
<i>Del Piero's dead.</i>

723
01:30:51,327 --> 01:30:52,362
What?

724
01:30:53,087 --> 01:30:54,759
<i>He poisoned himself.</i>

725
01:30:55,727 --> 01:30:56,762
What?

726
01:30:56,927 --> 01:30:59,839
<i>He was found
at the edge of the swimming pool.</i>

727
01:31:02,327 --> 01:31:05,160
He poisoned himself?

728
01:31:09,007 --> 01:31:10,122
Was there a note?

729
01:31:10,287 --> 01:31:11,322
<i>No.</i>

730
01:31:13,207 --> 01:31:14,196
Who found him?

731
01:31:14,367 --> 01:31:18,645
Susanna. I've got to go.
I'm there now.

732
01:31:24,087 --> 01:31:26,362
Okay, okay.

733
01:33:06,647 --> 01:33:08,365
Did you call Giovanni?

734
01:33:16,687 --> 01:33:18,598
I lost a friend,

735
01:33:21,247 --> 01:33:25,206
in Boscoreale.
Marty Del Piero.

736
01:33:29,047 --> 01:33:31,117
We worked together in New York,

737
01:33:32,967 --> 01:33:34,798
a long time ago.

738
01:33:39,767 --> 01:33:42,565
I'm through here.
I want to go home.

739
01:33:44,607 --> 01:33:46,916
Tomorrow, after the funeral.

740
01:34:12,367 --> 01:34:15,325
You little prick!

741
01:34:18,367 --> 01:34:22,246
Are you fuckin' trying to kill me?
Are you crazy?

742
01:34:32,807 --> 01:34:35,241
Mommy, I can't find Ettore.

743
01:34:42,607 --> 01:34:44,120
Ettore! Ettore!

744
01:34:59,247 --> 01:35:01,283
Where's Ettore?

745
01:35:21,887 --> 01:35:23,081
Tina.

746
01:35:25,167 --> 01:35:28,204
- Love, did you see Ettore leave?
- No.

747
01:35:37,927 --> 01:35:39,406
Ettore!

748
01:36:25,247 --> 01:36:26,919
Giovanni, it's Jessie.

749
01:36:27,087 --> 01:36:30,238
I can't find Ettore anywhere.
I don't know what's happened.

750
01:36:31,847 --> 01:36:33,678
Do you know where Matt is?

751
01:36:35,687 --> 01:36:37,757
Could you come over right away?

752
01:36:39,967 --> 01:36:42,003
Yes, right away. Thank you.

753
01:36:56,767 --> 01:36:58,166
Matt!

754
01:36:59,487 --> 01:37:01,717
Ettore has disappeared,

755
01:37:02,127 --> 01:37:05,403
Giovanni thinks
he might have gone to Ginostra.

756
01:38:34,647 --> 01:38:36,763
Jessie, Jessie.

757
01:38:40,287 --> 01:38:42,357
Is there any news of Ettore?

758
01:38:43,927 --> 01:38:45,838
Calm down.

759
01:38:49,247 --> 01:38:51,715
We'll find him. I promise you.

760
01:38:52,367 --> 01:38:55,564
Don't worry. He just needed
to get away, okay?

761
01:38:55,887 --> 01:38:57,957
Where's Matt?
Is the funeral over?

762
01:38:58,127 --> 01:39:02,166
He's probably with the magistrates.
All the officials were there.

763
01:39:03,367 --> 01:39:07,155
People want to get to know Matt.
Especially his methods.

764
01:39:07,327 --> 01:39:10,160
I need to find Matt.
I need to tell him about Ettore.

765
01:39:10,327 --> 01:39:13,956
You will. I am going to Ginostra.
Ettore must have gone back there.

766
01:39:14,687 --> 01:39:17,520
I called the helicopter,
it's arriving.

767
01:39:18,007 --> 01:39:20,680
But, I need the car.

768
01:39:22,847 --> 01:39:25,964
But... Matt has mine.
I need to be able to leave.

769
01:39:26,127 --> 01:39:27,924
I can't just be left stranded here.

770
01:39:28,087 --> 01:39:30,920
Matt will be back soon.
Don't worry.

771
01:39:31,087 --> 01:39:34,557
You have to stay here anyay.
In case Ettore comes back.

772
01:39:37,207 --> 01:39:38,606
I need the car.

773
01:39:47,087 --> 01:39:48,486
Thank you.

774
01:40:01,087 --> 01:40:04,318
Let's go. Quickly.
Go, go.

775
01:44:02,007 --> 01:44:03,645
Ettore!

776
01:44:07,207 --> 01:44:09,357
Ettore! Stop!

777
01:44:11,367 --> 01:44:12,925
Ettore!

778
01:44:19,727 --> 01:44:22,719
- What you doing? Are you alright?
- Let go of me.

779
01:44:26,167 --> 01:44:27,646
I killed Manzella.

780
01:44:32,647 --> 01:44:34,000
I'm free now.

781
01:44:35,127 --> 01:44:36,799
You took my gun.

782
01:45:11,247 --> 01:45:13,966
It's starting to wake up.
We need to evacuate. Call the base.

783
01:45:14,127 --> 01:45:17,164
Icarus to base,
Icarus to base...

784
01:45:17,327 --> 01:45:20,080
The volcano is erupting
we must evacuate the island.

785
01:45:20,247 --> 01:45:21,965
I repeat.
We must evacuate the island.

786
01:45:28,847 --> 01:45:31,441
I see a car.
It's Manzella's car.

787
01:45:31,607 --> 01:45:35,236
You see the body?
I see a body by the car. Lower!

788
01:45:35,407 --> 01:45:37,204
I can't. There's a side wind.

789
01:45:37,367 --> 01:45:39,562
That's Benson's car.

790
01:45:41,207 --> 01:45:42,879
Lower!

791
01:45:47,207 --> 01:45:49,323
The body is Manzella.

792
01:45:49,647 --> 01:45:51,285
Get out of here. Now!

793
01:46:43,407 --> 01:46:44,681
Ettore!

794
01:46:45,367 --> 01:46:46,766
What's happening?

795
01:46:48,327 --> 01:46:51,239
- We're getting out of here.
- What about Ettore?

796
01:46:52,167 --> 01:46:53,441
What about him?

797
01:46:54,487 --> 01:46:56,079
- I'm letting him go.
- But I thought...

798
01:46:56,247 --> 01:46:57,600
- It's all over.
- Matt...

799
01:46:57,767 --> 01:47:00,122
- He's Giovanni's problem now.
- Tell me what's happening!

800
01:47:00,287 --> 01:47:01,515
Start packing!

801
01:47:31,847 --> 01:47:33,565
My car slipped into the crater

802
01:47:34,327 --> 01:47:37,956
and crashed into Manzella's pick-up.

803
01:47:40,327 --> 01:47:44,525
They will accuse me of his murder
when they find the two cars.

804
01:47:45,487 --> 01:47:48,877
I'll say it was me,
it's the truth.

805
01:47:53,207 --> 01:47:56,802
I am a criminal because
I'm keeping a criminal in my house.

806
01:48:03,567 --> 01:48:05,125
Get the hell out of here.

807
01:48:06,047 --> 01:48:09,119
- You're free.
- Where do you want me to go?

808
01:48:09,567 --> 01:48:13,480
- They want to kill me.
- I'll tell them you ran away.

809
01:48:34,807 --> 01:48:36,320
It's Giovanni.

810
01:48:40,127 --> 01:48:42,766
They've come to arrest him.

811
01:48:50,207 --> 01:48:51,845
What did you do?

812
01:48:52,567 --> 01:48:55,684
I'm not a murderer.
A revenge is not a murder.

813
01:49:12,647 --> 01:49:14,444
Matt, stop them!

814
01:49:16,127 --> 01:49:17,879
Don't let them land.

815
01:50:33,727 --> 01:50:35,319
Bastard!

816
01:51:21,407 --> 01:51:24,046
I can't. I can't get it down.

817
01:51:57,727 --> 01:51:59,524
Elena!

818
01:52:04,447 --> 01:52:05,880
Elena!

819
01:52:12,567 --> 01:52:15,161
Elena! Elena!

820
01:52:15,487 --> 01:52:16,920
Elena!

821
01:52:26,007 --> 01:52:27,281
Elena!

822
01:52:37,167 --> 01:52:38,600
Elena!

823
01:52:43,927 --> 01:52:48,842
What are you doing?
We must leave. They're evacuating.

824
01:52:49,007 --> 01:52:51,760
No, I've been waiting for years.

825
01:52:57,047 --> 01:52:59,277
I've got to get Matt.
He killed Manzella.

826
01:52:59,967 --> 01:53:04,279
The volcano is going to fuck me.
I have to get a picture of the cars.

827
01:53:04,927 --> 01:53:07,760
- Elena, come on!
- No, no.

828
01:53:18,487 --> 01:53:20,523
Come on lamb, come on.

829
01:53:50,127 --> 01:53:51,765
Come on lamby.

830
01:53:52,087 --> 01:53:53,725
Come on lamby, let's play.

831
01:53:54,247 --> 01:53:57,444
If the lave covers the evidence,
I'm screwed.

832
01:53:59,607 --> 01:54:01,359
Where's your damn camera?

833
01:54:07,327 --> 01:54:08,840
He didn't do it.

834
01:54:11,767 --> 01:54:13,246
What?

835
01:54:14,207 --> 01:54:17,199
I was with Matt. He was here,
at the time Manzella disappeared.

836
01:54:17,527 --> 01:54:19,324
What are you talking about?

837
01:54:21,047 --> 01:54:22,958
You heard me.

838
01:54:28,087 --> 01:54:29,679
You fucked him?

839
01:54:32,207 --> 01:54:36,405
I didn't say that. I said he didn't
kill Manzella. He is innocent.

840
01:54:38,127 --> 01:54:40,687
What about you?
Are you innocent too?

841
01:54:44,967 --> 01:54:48,084
- Bitch!
- If you insist, I'll testify.

842
01:54:48,487 --> 01:54:51,445
You fucking bitch!

843
01:55:23,647 --> 01:55:25,160
We're safe here.

844
01:55:26,807 --> 01:55:30,197
Even if there is a tidal wave.
We're on high ground.

845
01:55:31,607 --> 01:55:33,484
The guards have left!

846
01:55:35,447 --> 01:55:38,678
- They obey Giovanni.
- Come on lamby, come on.

847
01:55:39,607 --> 01:55:41,518
Come and play with me.

848
01:55:42,367 --> 01:55:46,838
Come on lamby, come on.
Come on lamby,

849
01:55:47,487 --> 01:55:50,285
Mommy, mommy, come and see,
the lamby's sick.

850
01:55:52,447 --> 01:55:55,598
Maybe you played with it too much.
It's not a toy.

851
01:56:24,127 --> 01:56:26,118
- It's a bomb.
- What?

852
01:56:26,807 --> 01:56:29,560
They've put a bomb in it.
Get away!

853
01:56:29,727 --> 01:56:30,796
What?

854
01:56:35,247 --> 01:56:36,760
It's all right.

855
01:57:25,327 --> 01:57:29,320
Mommy, what's happening?
I'm scared.

856
01:57:50,847 --> 01:57:52,280
Jessie!

857
01:57:56,887 --> 01:58:00,118
It's all over. Sweetheart.
You alright?

858
01:58:00,527 --> 01:58:02,518
Okay, okay, sweetheart?

859
01:58:03,367 --> 01:58:05,358
You okay? It's alright.

860
01:58:05,607 --> 01:58:07,677
It's all over.

861
01:58:09,127 --> 01:58:10,606
It's all over.

862
01:58:11,207 --> 01:58:12,640
It's all over now.

863
02:00:26,287 --> 02:00:27,879
It's done.

864
02:01:05,807 --> 02:01:09,436
This is Benson. Tell him to come
and get us at the Villa Massina.

865
02:01:09,607 --> 02:01:11,996
The boy's back.
He's okay.

866
02:01:16,607 --> 02:01:18,120
Tell him to hurry.

867
02:01:41,727 --> 02:01:43,285
Fucking weather.

868
02:01:44,087 --> 02:01:47,443
Ginostra wakes up
and everything goes to hell.

869
02:01:49,247 --> 02:01:50,919
I know what you did.

870
02:01:53,607 --> 02:01:55,040
What did I do?

871
02:01:57,607 --> 02:02:00,075
Forget it.
I've come for the boy.

872
02:02:00,807 --> 02:02:04,277
Manzella's dead.
I'm responsible for him.

873
02:02:04,567 --> 02:02:07,081
You can't keep him here any longer.

874
02:02:10,847 --> 02:02:14,283
- I'll bring him back tomorrow.
- No, no. I'll take him.

875
02:02:20,567 --> 02:02:22,558
Let him get his things.

876
02:02:23,527 --> 02:02:26,405
Someone is going to
come and get his stuff tomorrow.

877
02:02:30,687 --> 02:02:33,281
- I'll get his coat.
- What?

878
02:02:34,047 --> 02:02:36,003
Matt, what are you doing?

879
02:02:39,887 --> 02:02:41,161
Matt!

880
02:03:41,287 --> 02:03:42,606
Giovanni!

881
02:03:44,207 --> 02:03:45,526
Giovanni!

882
02:03:47,367 --> 02:03:48,595
Give me the boy!

883
02:03:50,807 --> 02:03:52,923
- Give me the boy.
- What?

884
02:03:53,647 --> 02:03:56,844
- Come on. I'll bring him tomorrow!
- What are you talking about?

885
02:03:59,367 --> 02:04:01,198
Matt, Matt!

886
02:04:03,447 --> 02:04:05,597
Matt! Help me!

887
02:04:08,207 --> 02:04:09,526
Matt!

888
02:04:10,327 --> 02:04:11,442
Matt!

889
02:04:12,407 --> 02:04:15,046
He's chained me. Help!

890
02:04:17,367 --> 02:04:19,597
Matt, help me!

891
02:04:20,687 --> 02:04:22,405
They are coming to get me.

892
02:04:23,927 --> 02:04:25,724
What are you doing? Stop it!

893
02:04:38,367 --> 02:04:41,564
Ettore! Brake the light!

894
02:04:44,407 --> 02:04:47,080
The stones in your pocket!

895
02:04:48,687 --> 02:04:50,200
Break the light!

896
02:05:10,167 --> 02:05:11,759
- Bastard!
- Matt.

897
02:06:21,887 --> 02:06:23,525
Take his gun!

898
02:07:29,807 --> 02:07:31,445
Wash your hands.

899
02:07:35,367 --> 02:07:36,686
Wash them good.

900
02:07:41,247 --> 02:07:42,805
Giovanni is coming!

901
02:07:45,647 --> 02:07:48,400
It's not Giovanni.
It's for us.

902
02:07:49,647 --> 02:07:52,320
- We have to go right now.
- Where are we going?

903
02:07:52,847 --> 02:07:55,884
- Back to New York.
- What about Ettore?

904
02:07:56,247 --> 02:07:58,124
He's coming with us.

